The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump and Education Secretary Betsy DeVos at a meeting in the White House. The President congratulates DeVos on becoming the Education Secretary and expresses his commitment to providing every child in America with the opportunity to succeed. He discusses the need for education reform, particularly in disadvantaged communities, and highlights the success of charter schools in improving education outcomes. The President also mentions his focus on bringing back jobs to the country and the importance of education in creating better job opportunities. The Education Secretary expresses her gratitude for the opportunity to serve and emphasizes the need for equal access to quality education for all children. The meeting includes discussions with parents and educators representing various types of schools, including public, charter, homeschools, and private schools.